This recipe is a huge hit with my family. I've made it several times. We're dairy-free due to allergies, so I subbed coconut milk. Delish. It does need a lot of salt and pepper though, and I usually use more bacon than the recipe calls for. Make sure to par-boil the potatoes before you add them. It's not as thick as your traditional chowder, but still very tasty.

Rating: 2
I thought this was really bland. I simmered the potato longer than the suggested 5 minutes and I'm glad I did; it would have been undercooked otherwise. I had to add 1/2 tsp. salt and a lot of pepper because the soup was so bland. I added heavy cream (not half-and-half) and it was still thin. By no means was this horrible, but I had expeced it to be better.

Rating: 3
I had grilled up some white corn a couple days before & had defrosted a couple of chicken breasts & had all of the other ingredients, so I figured I'd give it a shot. This was SOOO frick'n easy & turned out GREAT (of course, w/some changes). I think that grilled sweet corn made a difference, you can taste a little of that smokey flavor (I also used a 1/2 cup more... 3 ears).I also prefer white meat. I added at least 1 tsp more of thyme & added almost 1 tsp of cayenne pepper to give it a little heat. I didn't use any salt because I made some extra bacon, mixing it into the soup & using it as garnish as well. The last change I made was to use heavy whipping cream instead of half & half. I'll for sure make this again.... ok recipe, but if you take liberties you can definitely make this a hit!

