My 15 year old daughter would like this at least once a week, in every season. I have made this for sick friends, a new mother just out of the hospital, and for informal dinner parties. It is wonderful! I dress it up with an orange and arugala salad with sweet and sour dressing, french bread, and a yummy dessert, or just serve it for family with the bread. UPDATE My daughter is now 20 and just emailed me for the recipe. USE CHIKEN THIGHS. I laugh at the people who get so complicated cooking their chicken breasts and then say the soup needs more flavor. I add a little more chicken than asked for, but other than that, "Don't mess with success"!

