Rating: 4
I really like this recipe. But I have to admit that I added a couple of things, I chopped a small jalapeno pepper and sauteed it with the onion. I used only white meat, and sauteed it before adding the stock. I also added a little bit of cornstarch to thicken it up a bit (but agree with another reviewer that next time I'll mash the potatoes), and a couple of squirts of tabasco. I didn't have fresh thyme on hand, so I used dried. I'm sure that fresh would have been better, but this was an easy and delicious weeknight supper (and today's lunch). ;-)

Rating: 4
This isn't a soup, it's truly a meal. I doubled the ingrediants and used split chicked breasts. I also used a Chicken Base to create the broth. Started this early in the day, removed the chicked and de-boned, and allowed the broth to simmer very low heat till just before dinner. Increased the heat and added the remaining ingrediants, including Half and Half and simmered for half an hour. My friends raved. Surved with a Crusty Bread. This is a keeper.

Rating: 4
I don't know why this recipe doesn't have a higher rating: it is fantastic! Granted, it was the first and only time I've ever made Corn Chowder, but I found it absolutely delicious! I brought it to work and everyone just loved it and wanted the recipe. I did make some changes: I used one onion and 3 slices of bacon, but doubled the chicken stock, corn, dried thyme and 1/2 and 1/2. Used only white meat. I can't believe how delicious it turned out for such a simple recipe. A classic and an instant keeper!

